                     <interp inst="t17840707-102-off499" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840707-102-off499" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               he having in his custody and possession a certain Bill of Exchange, with the names Watkins and Smith subscribed thereto, purporting to bear date at Daintree the 21st of April, directed to Messrs. Boldero and Co. Bankers in London, for payment of twenty-three pounds to Mr. 
                     <persName id="t17840707-102-person1031">
                        John
                         Churchill
                     <interp inst="t17840707-102-person1031" type="surname" value="Churchill"></interp>
